 SP14 work shirts. PT20 industrial pants. CS10 coveralls for fleet techs. Embroidered logo on the left, name patch on the right. The uniform standard for Vegas mechanic shops and trade fleets — without the rental-program markup.
 </p>

 <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
 <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary text-base">
 Get a Quote
 <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
 </a>
 <a href="tel:+17029048923" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-2 py-3 font-mono text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-white transition-colors hover:text-gold-400">
 702.904.8923
 </a>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Why Red Kap — concrete -->
 <section class="bg-concrete py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">Why Red Kap</p>
 <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Four reasons fleet shops pick it <span class="text-gold-600">every time.</span></h2>
 </div>

 <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
 {why.map((w) => (
 <div class="border border-hairline bg-panel p-7 transition-colors hover:border-gold-500">
 <h3 class="mb-3 font-heading text-xl font-bold uppercase leading-tight tracking-tight text-charcoal">{w.title}</h3>
 <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-ash">{w.body}</p>
 </div>
 ))}
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Deep dive — paper -->
 <section class="border-y border-hairline bg-paper py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">The Buyer's Guide</p>
 <h2 class="mb-8 font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase leading-tight tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-4xl">
 Why Red Kap is the spec for Las Vegas mechanical, HVAC, and fleet uniform programs.
 </h2>

 <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 <p>
 Red Kap is the dominant brand for industrial uniform programs across Las Vegas — mechanical contractors, HVAC techs, plumbers, fleet drivers, automotive service, and industrial maintenance crews all spec Red Kap because the construction holds up to industrial laundry cycles, the sizing runs consistent year over year, and the styling reads as "professional trade" rather than "promo company." When a service tech walks into a customer's home or a property manager's office, the Red Kap uniform sets the right impression on sight.
 </p>
 <p>
 The SP14 Industrial Work Shirt is the catalog workhorse — a 65/35 polyester-cotton button-front shirt with two chest pockets, available in short sleeve and long sleeve, in the colorways that move on Vegas trades (postman blue, charcoal, navy, light blue, white). We embroider company logos on the left chest and employee name patches on the right chest as a single coordinated decoration spec. For HVAC and mechanical shops that swap shirts between assigned techs, we sew on woven name patches that can be removed and reapplied without ruining the garment.
 </p>
 <p>
 For trades that need a tougher build, the SC30 Cotton Contrast Work Shirt and the CS70 Premium Industrial Work Shirt step up the construction quality. The SY24 Performance Plus Work Shirt is the moisture-wicking option for Vegas summer fieldwork — same cut as the SP14 but in a performance fabric that handles 110° service calls without becoming a heat liability. The PT20 Industrial Work Pant pairs with any of the shirts for a full uniform package, and we hem to spec on bulk orders so crews aren't wearing pants that drag through grease pits.
 </p>
 <p>
 For fleet and delivery operations, the SK24 Snap-Front Work Shirt is the most-ordered SKU — easier to take on and off in a service van than a button front, and decoration takes embroidery cleanly on the chest panel above the snaps. We also stock the JT22 Insulated Duck Work Jacket for cold-weather route drivers and the JT38 Hydro Shield Lightweight Jacket for crews that work in inclement weather without wanting full rain gear bulk.
 </p>
 <p>
 The reason Red Kap works for industrial laundry is the construction. The seams are double-needle, the buttons are reinforced, and the fabric is engineered to retain color and shape through 200+ industrial wash cycles. If you're running a shirt-rental program with an industrial laundry partner, Red Kap is the de facto spec — most of the major industrial laundry companies in the Vegas market already process Red Kap shirts on standard programs. We can integrate with your laundry partner's coding system and pre-decorate shirts to match their inventory tagging.
 </p>
 <p>
 Our <a href="/blog/red-kap-industrial-work-shirts-buyer-guide/" class="text-gold-600 underline decoration-gold-500/40 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">Red Kap industrial work shirts buyer guide</a> walks through fits, fabrics, and which Red Kap line to pick.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Products — concrete -->
 <section class="bg-concrete py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">Most-Ordered</p>
 <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">The Red Kap items we run <span class="text-gold-600">every week.</span></h2>
 <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 We stock the SP14, PT20, and SC30 in core colors and adult sizes S–4XL. Coveralls, jackets, FR, and hi-vis we order in for your project.
 </p>
 </div>

 <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
 {products.map((p) => (
 <div class="border border-hairline bg-panel p-6 transition-colors hover:border-gold-500">
 <div class="mb-3 flex items-center justify-between">
 <span class="spec text-gold-600">{p.sku}</span>
 </div>
 <h3 class="mb-2 font-heading text-lg font-bold uppercase leading-tight tracking-tight text-charcoal">{p.name}</h3>
 <p class="mb-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ash">{p.detail}</p>
 <div class="mt-4 border-t border-hairline pt-3">
 <span class="spec text-gold-600">Decoration</span>
 <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-charcoal">{p.method}</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 ))}
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- vs Dickies — paper -->
 <section class="border-y border-hairline bg-paper py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <p class="kicker mb-3">vs Dickies / Generic Industrial</p>
 <h2 class="mb-8 font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-4xl">Why Red Kap holds up where Dickies wears out.</h2>

 <div class="overflow-hidden border border-hairline bg-panel">
 <table class="w-full">
 <thead class="bg-concrete">
 <tr class="border-b border-hairline">
 <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ash">&nbsp;</th>
 <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ash">Dickies / Generic</th>
 <th class="px-5 py-4 text-left font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-gold-600">Red Kap</th>
